Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Technique: WRITTEN WITH A REED PEN/REED WITH SPLIT NIB
Name: Literary papyrus
Description: Papyrus of which the presence of a certain Coronis (last line of the second column) and the possibility of an allusion to the Dactyls of the Ida (column II, line 1-2), remind one of a text of a literary nature, with perhaps a quotation of the haughtiness of Coronis (a nymph seduced by Apollo, the mother of Asklepios).
